<p>
<li><a name="eighty5">In fact</a>  the reality of imputed income is even more complex than the examples I have used. In Family A/B, a dual-income couple, assuming that women continue to bear a disproportionate share of housework, Mrs B may still be producing imputed income for the family despite working outside the home full-time. Conversely, in Family C/D, the fact that Mrs D stays at home does not necessarily mean that the family will not spend money on outside help for housework. These complications only add to the administrative impossibility of including imputed income in the income tax base.
<p>
