<p>
<li><a name="one32">It is interesting</a> to note that contemporary tax policy specialists debate over whether income tax provisions actually influence human behaviour, and, in particular, whether the marital exemption influences women not to enter the wage force. It is quite clear by the changes the government enacted in 1942 that the government of that day believed that income tax provisions could influence married women's decisions to enter waged work.
