<li><a name="one32">The particulars of the test are as follows:</a>
<ol>
<li>Is the legislative objective sufficiently &quot;pressing and substantial&quot; to justify the limitation of a <cite>Charter</cite> right?
<li>Are the means proportional to the ends sought? That is:
<ol type="a">
<li>Are the means rationally connected to the ends sought?
<li>Do the means chosen impair the right in question as little as possible?
<li>Are the effects of the means chosen proportional to the end sought?
