<li><a name="fourteen">Even by late 1991,</a> Israeli officials still believed that the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, General Command, under Ahmed Jabril, held primary responsibility for the bombing. See R.H. Kupperman &amp; T. Kupperman, &quot;Pan Am 103: Facts vs. Politics&quot; <cite>New York Times</cite> (16 November 1991) A19, and D. Johnston, &quot;Plane Blast Still Open Case, U.S. Says&quot; <cite>New York Times</cite> (26 November 1991) A12.
