<li><a name="one02">These two boundaries</a> are similar to those described by Judge Bedjaoui: (a) respect for the United Nations Charter, and (b) respect for general international law. Judge Bedjaoui regarded the first boundary as easier to implement than the second. See <cite>Libya v. U.S.</cite> (Prov. Meas.), <i>supra</i> note 6 at 155, paras. 25--6 (Bedjaoui, J., diss. op.). See also the dissenting opinion of Judge Bustamente in <cite>Certain Expenses</cite>, where he described validity as relying on the concurrence of (a) formal legality and (b) intrinsic
or substantive legality. <i>Supra</i>, note 95 at 290 (Bustamente, J., diss. op.).
