151. The comment is a paraphrase of Judge Robert H. Jackson's famous observation: &quot;[R]eversal by a higher court is not proof that justice is thereby better done. There is no doubt that if there were a super-Supreme Court, a substantial proportion of our reversals of state courts would also be reversed. We are not final because we are infallible, but we are infallible only because we are final.&quot; See <cite>Brown v. Allen</cite>, 344 U.S. 443 (1953) at 540.
