<html>
<head>
<title>UTLR  Vol. 51 No. 2: Abstract 3</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>[<a href="http://www.utoronto.ca/">University of Toronto</a>] [<a href="http://www.law.utoronto.ca/">Faculty of Law</a>] [<a href="http://www.law-lib.utoronto.ca/law-review/">Law Review</a>] [<a href="http://www.law-lib.utoronto.ca/law-review/index.htm#vol51#2">Volume 51 Number 2</a>]</center><p><br>

<h1> Imperium by the Back Door: The <cite>Astreinte</cite> and the Enforcement of Contractual Obligations in France
<p> 
 M.P. MICHELL</h1>
<p><br>
<center><h3>ABSTRACT</h3></center>

The author examines the historical development, theoretical foundations, and recent legislative grounding of the
<cite>astreinte</cite>, a judicial order in French law used for the specific enforcement of obligations and civil judgments. The author identifies contradictions between the theoretical purity of the <cite>Civil Code</cite> and the need for effective remedies, and shows how French courts, jurists, and legislators have attempted to deal with this conflict. The <cite>astreinte</cite> originated in judicial practice and its history has been driven by the courts.
<p>
L'auteur examine le d&eacute;veloppement historique, le fondement th&eacute;orique et la base l&eacute;gislative r&eacute;cente de l'astreinte, un genre d'ordonnance judiciaire en droit fran&ccedil;ais qui sert &agrave; l'ex&eacute;cution d'obligations et de jugements civils. Il fait &eacute;tat de certaines contradictions entre la puret&eacute; th&eacute;orique du Code civil et la n&eacute;cessit&eacute; de pr&eacute;voir des recours efficaces, et indique la fa&ccedil;on par laquelle les tribunaux, juristes et l&eacute;gislateurs fran&ccedil;ais ont tent&eacute; de r&eacute;soudre le probl&egrave;me. L'astreinte a son origine dans la pratique judiciaire et son
&eacute;volution est guid&eacute;e par les tribunaux.
<p><br>
<hr>
<address>
Updated and maintained by the <a href="http://www.law-lib.utoronto.ca/">Bora Laskin Law Library</a>.<br>
Please send comments and suggestions to <a href = "mailto:law.web@utoronto.ca">law.web@utoronto.ca</a>
