<li><a name="one">In this article</a> the term &quot;female circumcision&quot; will be used. Some authors consider this an incorrect term since it implies, falsely, an equivalency with male circumcision. However, the term &quot;genital mutilation&quot; is also controversial, since it is seen as entirely
negative and insensitive to circumcised women.
<p>
<li><a name="two"><cite>United Nations Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees</cite></a>, 28 July 1951, 189 U.N.T.S. 150, A.T.S. 5(1954) [hereinafter <cite>Geneva Convention</cite>].
