<HEAD>
<title>University of Toronto Faculty of Law December 1995 Examinations</title>
</HEAD>
<BODY link="#00562d" vlink="#440000">
<center><h1><a href="http://www.utoronto.ca/">University of Toronto</a><br><a href="http://www.law.utoronto.ca/">Faculty of Law</a></h1>
<h2>Torts I<br>
December 1995<br>
Professor Ernest Weinrib</h2></center>
<h3>NOTE:</h3>
<ol>
<li>This is an open-book examination. You may make use of any books, notes, or papers.<p>
<li>PLEASE WRITE ON ALTERNATE LINES!<p>
<li>Before you begin, ensure that you have written your pseudonym, course name, and the number of the booklet on <b>each</b> examination booklet and the name of the instructor on the <b>first</b> booklet. If you request an additional booklet(s) during the examination, write the required information on the booklet at the time you receive it. No time will be permitted for this at the end of the examination.<p>
<li>During the examination, only one student at a time is permitted to leave the examination room. No student may leave within fifteen minutes of the conclusion of the examination.<p>
<li>At the end of this examination, the invigilator will ask you to stop writing, count the total number of booklets used, record this on the front of the first booklet, and insert all booklets into the first booklet. You will then gather your belongings and leave the examination room. <b>All examination answer booklets are to be left on the writing table and will be collected by the invigilator.</b><p>
<li>Time limits will be strictly enforced. Students who continue to write after the examination has ended will have their answer booklets collected separately and may be subject to a penalty.
</ol>
<hr>
<p><br>
<dd>The Peters family has a vacation home in Bel Sol, a summer resort community that was recently constructed in the wilderness north of the city of Flavelle. The water for this home comes from a well that was dug beside it. This water, however, has now become undrinkable for two reasons, either of which by itself would have sufficed to ruin the water.
<p>
<dd>The first reason is that the Thanatos Chemical Works factory, a few kilometres from Bel Sol, spews forth pollution that falls to the earth with every rainfall and then contaminates the sources for the wells at Bel Sol. The Thanatos Chemical Works has been at this location for decades. Indeed, it set up its factory here in order to be far from any urban districts that might complain about the deleterious effects of its pollution. The only other inhabitants of this area are the residents of the town of Styx, from which Thanatos draws its work force. The water in Styx is also undrinkable, but Thanatos has a longstanding arrangement with the residents of Styx under which Thanatos delivers bottled water free. Thanatos is willing in the future to extend this arrangement to the Peters family and other vacationers in Bel Sol. The value of Thanatos' investment in its factory far exceeds the value of all the vacation homes in Bel Sol, and Thanatos is the only employer in the area.
<p>
<dd>The second reason is an incident that happened shortly after the Peters family went to Bel Sol for the first time. A package was delivered to them by Courier Express Co. The Courier driver left his truck idling while he went through the formalities of having the package signed for. While this was going on, the Peters' neighbours' eight-year-old son, Dennis, climbed into the truck and began to play with the steering wheel and the levers. He unknowingly released the emergency brake, and when the truck began to move, he chortled with delight and began to steer it. The truck left the road and came to a stop on the lawn beside the Peters house, exactly over the septic tank. The septic tank is usually strong enough to bear a heavy weight, but a few moments before the delivery there had been a very slight earth tremor that did no noticeable damage but weakened the septic tank, so that the tank cracked when the truck came to rest above it. The material in the septic tank then oozed out and contaminated the well, which was beside it.
<p>
<dd>The Peters now want to sue Thanatos, Courier, and Dennis for damages, and they want an injunction against Thanatos. Discuss the tort issues that arise on these facts. Where appropriate, set out the different possible approaches to liability and briefly assess the justice or the desirability of these approaches.
<p><br>
<hr>
